Kenya on Tuesday recorded 72 new cases of Covid-19, raising the country's total number to 2,093, Health CAS Rashid Aman has said. The cases are from 2,892 samples tested in the last 24 hours. A total of 39 are from Nairobi, while 13 are from Busia. The youngest is 11 years and oldest is 73. Another 17 patients have been discharged, raising the recoveries to 499. On a sad note, another two people have died, raising the deaths to 71. Aman hit out at truck drivers not following guidelines. "If you do this you will create congestion and create problems for yourselves," he said. More follows...